Dominica has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Dominica, see Return to the UK
Local measures
A State of Emergency is in place but restrictions are being gradually eased. A pass system is in operation, obtainable from the Dominica Police.
From 6 pm to 6 am and on Sundays, nobody can go out unless offering or accessing an essential service. On Mondays to Fridays, people can access or provide retail services including supermarkets, medical, gas stations, clothing and textile, appliances and electronics stores. On Saturdays permitted retail outlets may open 8 am to 1 pm.
It is mandatory to wear masks outside the home. Beaches and rivers may be accessed 8 am to 5 pm Monday to Saturday but no alcohol consumption, picnics, music or gatherings of more than 10 people are permitted. Schools, bars and churches remain closed.
For more information, go to the Dominica Government Information Service on Facebook
See Return to the UK
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
